Simple support for Go testing with a live Postgres database
----

This package makes it straightforward to write tests that connect
to a fresh Postgres database created for the tests.

## Set up ##
In order to use pgtest, you'll need to setup your postgres user as follow:

```
sudo -u postgres createuser someuser
sudo -u postgres psql
psql (10.5 (Ubuntu 10.5-0ubuntu0.18.04))
Type "help" for help.

postgres=# alter user someuser with password 'somepassword';
ALTER ROLE
postgres=# create database someuser;
CREATE DATABASE
postgres=# grant all on database someuser to someuser;
GRANT
postgres=# \q
export PGPASSWORD=somepassword
export PGUSER=someuser
```
